  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">219028_BORESHA III - Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Boresha Phase III will be the last phase of this EU funded action and is a follow on of Phase II; will build on the achievements of the current action with focus on sustainability/exit strategy, including the cross-border dimension of the proposed intervention and addressing the recommendations from EU ROM report. An ammendment to the proposal was made to cover drought related response activities. 
 
 The Cross-border region encompassing north-eastern Kenya, south-eastern Ethiopia and south-western Somalia, also known as the Mandera Triangle, is a critical intersectional area for stability, peace and economic integration within the Horn of Africa. The Mandera Triangle region, as a point of convergence, is known for its instability, influx of refugees and many IDPs, recurrent conflicts and climate shocks, as well as being home to one of the most underprivileged and marginalized populations within Africa.
 
 The main objective is: to promote economic development and greater resilience, particularly among vulnerable groups in Mandera Triangle.
 
 The 3 main outcomes are;
 
  Outcome 1: Communities in the Mandera Triangle are more resilient and better prepared for shocks, and response is more effective 
 
  Outcome 2: Communities in the Mandera Triangle are more resilient and better prepared for shocks, and response is more effective 
 
 Outcome 3: Cross-border rangeland and other shared natural resources are more equitably and sustainably managed</narrative>
  </description>
